{"name":"Mathlib.Combinatorics.Hall.Finite","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Data.Fintype.Basic","Mathlib.Data.Set.Finite"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.lean#L260-L272","name":"Finset.all_card_le_biUnion_card_iff_existsInjective'","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.html#Finset.all_card_le_biUnion_card_iff_existsInjective'","doc":"This is the version of **Hall's Marriage Theorem** in terms of indexed\nfamilies of finite sets `t : ι → Finset α` with `ι` finite.\nIt states that there is a set of distinct representatives if and only\nif every union of `k` of the sets has at least `k` elements.\n\nSee `Finset.all_card_le_biUnion_card_iff_exists_injective` for a version\nwhere the `Finite ι` constraint is removed.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.lean#L230-L247","name":"HallMarriageTheorem.hall_hard_inductive","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.html#HallMarriageTheorem.hall_hard_inductive","doc":"Here we combine the two inductive steps into a full strong induction proof,\ncompleting the proof the harder direction of **Hall's Marriage Theorem**.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.lean#L170-L219","name":"HallMarriageTheorem.hall_hard_inductive_step_B","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.html#HallMarriageTheorem.hall_hard_inductive_step_B","doc":"Second case of the inductive step: assuming that\n`∃ (s : Finset ι), s ≠ univ → s.card = (s.biUnion t).card`\nand that the statement of **Hall's Marriage Theorem** is true for all\n`ι'` of cardinality ≤ `n`, then it is true for `ι` of cardinality `n + 1`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.lean#L139-L162","name":"HallMarriageTheorem.hall_cond_of_compl","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.html#HallMarriageTheorem.hall_cond_of_compl","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.lean#L128-L136","name":"HallMarriageTheorem.hall_cond_of_restrict","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.html#HallMarriageTheorem.hall_cond_of_restrict","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.lean#L81-L124","name":"HallMarriageTheorem.hall_hard_inductive_step_A","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.html#HallMarriageTheorem.hall_hard_inductive_step_A","doc":"First case of the inductive step: assuming that\n`∀ (s : Finset ι), s.Nonempty → s ≠ univ → s.card < (s.biUnion t).card`\nand that the statement of **Hall's Marriage Theorem** is true for all\n`ι'` of cardinality ≤ `n`, then it is true for `ι` of cardinality `n + 1`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.lean#L53-L73","name":"HallMarriageTheorem.hall_cond_of_erase","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Finite.html#HallMarriageTheorem.hall_cond_of_erase","doc":""}]}